The paper deals with graph theory and its applications in quantum secret sharing protocols. Specifically, it introduces and studies the concept of weak odd domination in graphs and its connection to perfect codes and quantum secret sharing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Graph Theory).
